[2] Guinea (Fria): new cases
Date: Fri 5 Jun 2015
Source: Guinee News [in French, trans. Mod.JW, edited]
http://guineenews.org/ebola-fait-des-ravages-a-fria-11-cas-confirmes-106-contacts-officiel


Fria Prefecture, located 160 km from the Guinean capital, is on the alert since the 11th confirmed case in the rural commune Banguigni, reported in your online newspaper on Fri 5 Jun 2015. Supported by international partners involved in the fight against the hemorrhagic virus, the coordination of the struggle against Ebola, headed by Dr Barry, health director of the Prefecture of Fria, is working hard every day to eradicate this virus. Fria was already facing an economic crisis in 2012 following the closure of the alumina plant, nurturer of the city.

Dr Amadou Barry has told us: "Fria recorded its 11th confirmed case of Ebola on 26 May 2015, in a sick person from Banguigni in the locality of Horokilentcho who contracted the disease on one of several trips to Tchontchen in Telimele, and who returned ill and passed away a few weeks later; sampling was done afterwards, and the result was positive. Since then, we have identified 106 cases contacts that are being followed in the village of Horoguilinto in the sub-prefecture of Banguigni."

On the question of the difficulties associated with resistance, Dr Barry added: "Access to the village has not been easy; it took the intervention of the prefectural authority and citizens so that we could access the site to identify contacts, and occasionally the vehicle has been damaged by stoning. We still encounter some small resistance; there are also 7 people who have fled, and luckily the authorities and citizens are on the right track, because the research is around the village of the urban commune of Fria, according to our information."

[byline: Sheik Alpha Ibrahima Camara, special envoy to Fria]

